@@TJvUCBDisplayMode
<TITLE TJvUCBDisplayMode type>
Summary
  Specifies from which registry key(s) to read information.
Description
  The TJvUCBDisplayMode type is used to specify the registry hives to read uninstall information from.
  Windows can store uninstall info in two different hives, HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE and HKEY_CURRENT_USER.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvUCBDisplayMode.hkCurrentUser
  Read uninstall information from the HKEY_CURRENT_USER hive.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvUCBDisplayMode.hkLocalMachine
  Read uninstall information from the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE hive.

