@@TJvUninstallComboBox
<TITLEIMG TJvUninstallComboBox>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.EditsMemosAndCombos.Combos
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  A combobox that displays uninstall information.
Description
  Use a TJvUninstallComboBox when you need to display uninstall information to the end-user in a
  compact, space efficient way. The TJvUninstallComboBox control has several properties to control what
  do display. Modify DisplayMode to specify what registry hives to read uninstall information from, set
  ShowAll as appropriate to show or hide "unfriendly" entries. Set Sorted to true to sort the list.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvUninstallComboBox.DisplayMode
Summary
  Specify what registry hive or hives to read uninstall info from.
Description
  Use DisplayMode to specify the hives the component reads information from. If DisplayMode is set to
  an empty set, no information is shown.
See Also
  TJvUCBDisplayModes

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvUninstallComboBox.DisplayName
Summary
  Contains the display name of the currently selected item in the control.
Description
  \Read DisplayName to retrieve the "user friendly" name of the currently selected item in the control.
  If no item is selected, this property returns an empty string.

